
<p>Before you publish anything onto WordPress, make sure your user profile is up to snuff so readers can see your bio and pretty face at the bottom of each post.</p>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-5">
    <p class="small-caps">PUT IT INTO PRACTICE:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        From the dashboard, select Profile > Your Profile from the left sidebar.
      </li>
      <li>
        Update your first and last name (if necessary) and change your display name to “First Last.”
      </li>
      <li>
        Write a short bio about yourself. This will show up on all of your posts. Talk about yourself in the third person.
      </li>
      <li>
        Create a password (if necessary).
      </li>
      <li>
        Upload an avatar (preferably a pic of yourself). This will show up on all of your posts.
      </li>
      <li>
        Feel free to add whatever additional info you want.
      </li>
    </ol>
